CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 16, 1951, pg. 9 reads: "...Pitt Queen - At the annual...ceremonies at the University of Pittsburgh...ay, Elaine Hall, shown in ....an attendant to the "Senior Queen" at the coronation ceremony in the Commons Room. Miss Hall was graduated from the college on Wednesday. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Three woman wearing light colored full length dresses and crowns, including "Senior Queen," center, and Virginia Elaine Hall, right, walking along sidewalk with flower petals on Soldiers and Sailors lawn, with people and Pittsburgh Athletic Association building in background
